<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880804-0045 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Nipsco Industries Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NI </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   Northern Indiana Public Service Co., Hammond, Ind., said it is offering to purchase shares outstanding of two series of its cumulative preferred stock.    The utility, a unit of Nipsco Industries Inc., said it will buy any and all shares of its 7.44% series of preferred, in which there are 176,650 shares outstanding, at $88.50 a share. The unit also said it will purchase any and all shares of its 7.50% series of preferred, in which there are 200,696 shares outstanding, at $89.25 each.    The company said the offer, which is scheduled to expire on Aug. 31, isn't conditioned upon any minimum number of preferred shares being tendered. </TEXT></DOC>